20	// Design pointers earned by the old estate:
21	//   - E-238 / caution.md C-138: exhausted free tiers once burned 30s x 3 retries x 3 gate attempts
22	//     waiting for answers that were never coming. THIS SHELL DOES NOT RETRY: one attempt per
23	//     provider, then fall over. Retry/backoff, if ever wanted, belongs inside an injected `call`,
24	//     never here, so a storm can never originate in the router.
25	//   - caution.md C-040 / Rule 9: every external step is wrapped in a hard Promise.race deadline.
26	//     `deadlineMs` is a CAP (Rule 8: never a floor - there is no minimum wait anywhere in this file).
27	//   - caution.md C-133 / Rule 12 gate 5: a quorum is drawn from genuinely distinct provider FAMILIES.
