122	// errText(e): a short message for a rejected provider call (the injected caller threw or its promise
123	// rejected). withDeadline already converts a rejection into a resolved { error } result, so no catch
124	// is needed in callProvider - the failure is a first-class value, never an uncaught throw.
125	function errText(e) {
